main event: A number of saucer-shaped objects were seen in the sky north of Oshkosh, Wisconsin on August 15, 1967.
interesting points: The objects, numbering around 9-10, varied in size and maneuvered in an unusual pattern, accelerating rapidly, stopping abruptly, and moving in a way that seemed to defy the laws of physics.
Observers thought the objects might be new aircraft or missiles, but the unusual maneuvers ruled out any known flying vehicles.
The objects were still visible when the observers had to discontinue their observations as it was getting dark.
The report includes a hand-drawn sketch of the unidentified object in the sky.
The case was submitted to Project Blue Book, the U.S. Air Force's UFO investigation program, but the available information was deemed insufficient for a scientific evaluation.
